  "text": "Modern calculations in the UK use the MCBEND Monte Carlo radiation transport code [CITATION_1] for direct 3-D calculations (or reconstruction of volumetric data from 2-D calculations [CITATION_2] ). The whole reactor core is modelled to ensure that all significant routes that neutrons may take through the complicated geometry are represented (in practice the core symmetry allows an octant with reflecting boundaries).",
